2026-04-21 02:40:01 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 1'] hypothesis_explanation='The physical removal of the switch indicator LED and its resistor in Control Module 1 creates an open circuit in the parallel branch. However, since the main current path through Control Module 1 (from input to output, via the switch) should NOT depend on the presence of the indicator LED or its resistor, the absence of these components should not normally prevent current flow to subsequent modules and the load. Given the symptoms (no indicator LEDs lit, lamp not on), it is possible that the internal wiring of Control Module 1 is such that the removal of these components breaks the circuit entirely, causing all downstream modules and the load to be disconnected from the power supply. Therefore, the root cause is likely an open circuit in Control Module 1 due to the missing switch indicator LED and resistor, rendering the whole chain inoperative.'
