2026-04-21 02:40:17 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 1 Switch Indicator LED Ports', 'Control Module 2 Switch Indicator LED Ports', 'Control Module 3 Switch Indicator LED Ports'] hypothesis_explanation='The removal of both the resistor and LED from the switch indicator circuit in Control Modules 1, 2, and 3 (leaving the indicator ports open) creates an open circuit across the indicator branch. In this design, the indicator branch forms a parallel path across the main power line inside the module; when these elements are missing and the ports are left open, the circuit at that module becomes open, breaking continuity for the whole main series circuit and preventing current from reaching subsequent modules and the load lamp. The root cause is the open circuit at the LED/resistor ports in these modules, not the modules themselves or the indicator elements. Repair requires bridging these ports so the main circuit is not interrupted.'
